Class Iterator<T>

java.lang.Object
Iterator<T>
Type Parameters:
T - This stands for generic class. A generic class is a class that can work with any data type, or in other words, we can say that it is independent of the data type.
public class Iterator<T>
extends java.lang.Object
Iterator class is used to loop through collections.

  • Method Details

    • hasNext

      public boolean hasNext()
      Method is used to check if there are more elements.
      Returns:
      Method returns true if the iterator has more elements.

    • hasPrior

      public boolean hasPrior()
      Method to check if there is a prior node.
      Returns:
      Return true if there is a "prior" element, otherwise returns false.

    • next

      public T next()
      Method to get data of the next node.
      Returns:
      Returns the "next" node (really the current one) and moves the Iterator forward by one node.

    • prior

      public T prior()
      Method to get data of the prior node.
      Returns:
      Returns the "prior" node (really the current one) and moves the Iterator backward by one node.

    • setToEnd

      public void setToEnd()
      Sets the last node to the current node.
